{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":742,"text":"So we humans have an extraordinary\npotential for goodness,"},{"time":7963,"text":"but also an immense power to do harm."},{"time":12363,"text":"Any tool can be used to build\nor to destroy."},{"time":18036,"text":"That all depends on our motivation."},{"time":21217,"text":"Therefore, it is all the more important"},{"time":24664,"text":"to foster an altruistic motivation\nrather than a selfish one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30508,"text":"So now we indeed are facing \nmany challenges in our times."},{"time":37008,"text":"Those could be personal challenges."},{"time":40325,"text":"Our own mind can be our best friend\nor our worst enemy."},{"time":46341,"text":"There's also societal challenges:"},{"time":49225,"text":"poverty in the midst of plenty,\ninequalities, conflict, injustice."},{"time":54924,"text":"And then there are the new challenges,\nwhich we don't expect."},{"time":59120,"text":"Ten thousand years ago, there were\nabout five million human beings on Earth."},{"time":63763,"text":"Whatever they could do,"},{"time":65373,"text":"the Earth's resilience \nwould soon heal human activities."},{"time":70559,"text":"After the Industrial\nand Technological Revolutions,"},{"time":73775,"text":"that's not the same anymore."},{"time":76008,"text":"We are now the major agent\nof impact on our Earth."},{"time":80073,"text":"We enter the Anthropocene,\nthe era of human beings."},{"time":84977,"text":"So in a way, if we were to say\nwe need to continue this endless growth,"},{"time":91970,"text":"endless use of material resources,"},{"time":95616,"text":"it's like if this man was saying --"},{"time":98514,"text":"and I heard a former head of state,\nI won't mention who, saying --"},{"time":103386,"text":"\"Five years ago, we were at\nthe edge of the precipice."},{"time":107395,"text":"Today we made a big step forward.\""},{"time":110587,"text":"So this edge is the same\nthat has been defined by scientists"},{"time":116590,"text":"as the planetary boundaries."},{"time":119244,"text":"And within those boundaries,\nthey can carry a number of factors."},{"time":123705,"text":"We can still prosper, humanity can still\nprosper for 150,000 years"},{"time":129231,"text":"if we keep the same stability of climate"},{"time":132563,"text":"as in the Holocene\nfor the last 10,000 years."},{"time":135721,"text":"But this depends on choosing\na voluntary simplicity,"},{"time":141479,"text":"growing qualitatively, not quantitatively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144160,"text":"So in 1900, as you can see,\nwe were well within the limits of safety."},{"time":150394,"text":"Now, in 1950 came the great acceleration."},{"time":155793,"text":"Now hold your breath, not too long,\nto imagine what comes next."},{"time":160762,"text":"Now we have vastly overrun\nsome of the planetary boundaries."},{"time":166907,"text":"Just to take biodiversity, \nat the current rate,"},{"time":170866,"text":"by 2050, 30 percent of all species \non Earth will have disappeared."},{"time":177288,"text":"Even if we keep their DNA in some fridge,\nthat's not going to be reversible."},{"time":183085,"text":"So here I am sitting"},{"time":184936,"text":"in front of a 7,000-meter-high, \n21,000-foot glacier in Bhutan."},{"time":190836,"text":"At the Third Pole, 2,000 glaciers\nare melting fast, faster than the Arctic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197987,"text":"So what can we do in that situation?"},{"time":202144,"text":"Well, however complex\npolitically, economically, scientifically"},{"time":209453,"text":"the question of the environment is,"},{"time":211851,"text":"it simply boils down to a question\nof altruism versus selfishness."},{"time":218678,"text":"I'm a Marxist of the Groucho tendency."},{"time":222287,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":223712,"text":"Groucho Marx said, \"Why should I care\nabout future generations?"},{"time":227121,"text":"What have they ever done for me?\""},{"time":229151,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":230647,"text":"Unfortunately, I heard\nthe billionaire Steve Forbes,"},{"time":235430,"text":"on Fox News, saying exactly \nthe same thing, but seriously."},{"time":238958,"text":"He was told about the rise of the ocean,"},{"time":241293,"text":"and he said, \"I find it absurd\nto change my behavior today"},{"time":244640,"text":"for something that will happen \nin a hundred years.\""},{"time":247695,"text":"So if you don't care\nfor future generations,"},{"time":250593,"text":"just go for it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253494,"text":"So one of the main challenges of our times"},{"time":256420,"text":"is to reconcile three time scales:"},{"time":259538,"text":"the short term of the economy,"},{"time":261683,"text":"the ups and downs of the stock market,\nthe end-of-the-year accounts;"},{"time":265915,"text":"the midterm of the quality of life --"},{"time":268621,"text":"what is the quality every moment of our \nlife, over 10 years and 20 years? --"},{"time":273945,"text":"and the long term of the environment."},{"time":277554,"text":"When the environmentalists\nspeak with economists,"},{"time":279903,"text":"it's like a schizophrenic dialogue,\ncompletely incoherent."},{"time":282982,"text":"They don't speak the same language."},{"time":285814,"text":"Now, for the last 10 years,\nI went around the world"},{"time":289354,"text":"meeting economists, scientists,\nneuroscientists, environmentalists,"},{"time":293452,"text":"philosophers, thinkers \nin the Himalayas, all over the place."},{"time":297912,"text":"It seems to me, there's only one concept"},{"time":301834,"text":"that can reconcile\nthose three time scales."},{"time":304794,"text":"It is simply having more\nconsideration for others."},{"time":309198,"text":"If you have more consideration for others,\nyou will have a caring economics,"},{"time":314099,"text":"where finance is at the service of society"},{"time":317051,"text":"and not society at the service of finance."},{"time":320319,"text":"You will not play at the casino"},{"time":322187,"text":"with the resources that people\nhave entrusted you with."},{"time":325073,"text":"If you have more consideration for others,"},{"time":327919,"text":"you will make sure\nthat you remedy inequality,"},{"time":331396,"text":"that you bring some kind \nof well-being within society,"},{"time":335136,"text":"in education, at the workplace."},{"time":337176,"text":"Otherwise, a nation that is\nthe most powerful and the richest"},{"time":340599,"text":"but everyone is miserable,\nwhat's the point?"},{"time":343686,"text":"And if you have more\nconsideration for others,"},{"time":345973,"text":"you are not going to ransack\nthat planet that we have"},{"time":349369,"text":"and at the current rate, we don't\nhave three planets to continue that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353703,"text":"So the question is,"},{"time":356056,"text":"okay, altruism is the answer,\nit's not just a novel ideal,"},{"time":360387,"text":"but can it be a real, pragmatic solution?"},{"time":363611,"text":"And first of all, does it exist,"},{"time":366469,"text":"true altruism, or are we so selfish?"},{"time":370213,"text":"So some philosophers thought\nwe were irredeemably selfish."},{"time":375553,"text":"But are we really all just like rascals?"},{"time":380765,"text":"That's good news, isn't it?"},{"time":383579,"text":"Many philosophers, \nlike Hobbes, have said so."},{"time":386108,"text":"But not everyone looks like a rascal."},{"time":389429,"text":"Or is man a wolf for man?"},{"time":392262,"text":"But this guy doesn't seem too bad."},{"time":395150,"text":"He's one of my friends in Tibet."},{"time":398073,"text":"He's very kind."},{"time":400312,"text":"So now, we love cooperation."},{"time":403937,"text":"There's no better joy \nthan working together, is there?"},{"time":408275,"text":"And then not only humans."},{"time":412350,"text":"Then, of course, there's\nthe struggle for life,"},{"time":414837,"text":"the survival of the fittest,\nsocial Darwinism."},{"time":419178,"text":"But in evolution, cooperation --\nthough competition exists, of course --"},{"time":425015,"text":"cooperation has to be much more creative\nto go to increased levels of complexity."},{"time":430732,"text":"We are super-cooperators \nand we should even go further."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435414,"text":"So now, on top of that,\nthe quality of human relationships."},{"time":441443,"text":"The OECD did a survey among 10 factors,\nincluding income, everything."},{"time":445925,"text":"The first one that people said,\nthat's the main thing for my happiness,"},{"time":449268,"text":"is quality of social relationships."},{"time":452621,"text":"Not only in humans."},{"time":455498,"text":"And look at those great-grandmothers."},{"time":458846,"text":"So now, this idea \nthat if we go deep within,"},{"time":464000,"text":"we are irredeemably selfish,"},{"time":466570,"text":"this is armchair science."},{"time":469224,"text":"There is not a single sociological study,"},{"time":471491,"text":"psychological study,\nthat's ever shown that."},{"time":474737,"text":"Rather, the opposite."},{"time":476697,"text":"My friend, Daniel Batson, \nspent a whole life"},{"time":480355,"text":"putting people in the lab\nin very complex situations."},{"time":483118,"text":"And of course we are sometimes selfish,\nand some people more than others."},{"time":487487,"text":"But he found that systematically,\nno matter what,"},{"time":490149,"text":"there's a significant number of people"},{"time":493149,"text":"who do behave altruistically,\nno matter what."},{"time":496504,"text":"If you see someone\ndeeply wounded, great suffering,"},{"time":499696,"text":"you might just help\nout of empathic distress --"},{"time":502318,"text":"you can't stand it, so it's better to help\nthan to keep on looking at that person."},{"time":506468,"text":"So we tested all that, and in the end, \nhe said, clearly people can be altruistic."},{"time":512344,"text":"So that's good news."},{"time":514284,"text":"And even further, we should look\nat the banality of goodness."},{"time":519896,"text":"Now look at here."},{"time":521600,"text":"When we come out, we aren't \ngoing to say, \"That's so nice."},{"time":524370,"text":"There was no fistfight while this mob \nwas thinking about altruism.\""},{"time":528937,"text":"No, that's expected, isn't it?"},{"time":531099,"text":"If there was a fistfight,\nwe would speak of that for months."},{"time":534278,"text":"So the banality of goodness is something\nthat doesn't attract your attention,"},{"time":537949,"text":"but it exists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539437,"text":"Now, look at this."},{"time":549253,"text":"So some psychologists said,"},{"time":552054,"text":"when I tell them I run 140 humanitarian \nprojects in the Himalayas"},{"time":555291,"text":"that give me so much joy,"},{"time":557545,"text":"they said, \"Oh, I see,\nyou work for the warm glow."},{"time":560799,"text":"That is not altruistic.\nYou just feel good.\""},{"time":563703,"text":"You think this guy,\nwhen he jumped in front of the train,"},{"time":566991,"text":"he thought, \"I'm going to feel\nso good when this is over?\""},{"time":569277,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":571563,"text":"But that's not the end of it."},{"time":573849,"text":"They say, well, but when\nyou interviewed him, he said,"},{"time":576391,"text":"\"I had no choice.\nI had to jump, of course.\""},{"time":579526,"text":"He has no choice. Automatic behavior.\nIt's neither selfish nor altruistic."},{"time":583407,"text":"No choice?"},{"time":584882,"text":"Well of course, this guy's\nnot going to think for half an hour,"},{"time":587844,"text":"\"Should I give my hand? Not give my hand?\""},{"time":589881,"text":"He does it. There is a choice,\nbut it's obvious, it's immediate."},{"time":593676,"text":"And then, also, there he had a choice."},{"time":596037,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":598738,"text":"There are people who had choice,\nlike Pastor André Trocmé and his wife,"},{"time":602500,"text":"and the whole village\nof Le Chambon-sur-Lignon in France."},{"time":605187,"text":"For the whole Second World War,\nthey saved 3,500 Jews,"},{"time":609135,"text":"gave them shelter,\nbrought them to Switzerland,"},{"time":611792,"text":"against all odds, at the risk\nof their lives and those of their family."},{"time":615237,"text":"So altruism does exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617394,"text":"So what is altruism?"},{"time":619119,"text":"It is the wish: May others be happy\nand find the cause of happiness."},{"time":623021,"text":"Now, empathy is the affective resonance\nor cognitive resonance that tells you,"},{"time":628266,"text":"this person is joyful,\nthis person suffers."},{"time":630977,"text":"But empathy alone is not sufficient."},{"time":634463,"text":"If you keep on being\nconfronted with suffering,"},{"time":636686,"text":"you might have empathic distress, burnout,"},{"time":639447,"text":"so you need the greater sphere\nof loving-kindness."},{"time":643507,"text":"With Tania Singer at the Max Planck \nInstitute of Leipzig,"},{"time":646234,"text":"we showed that the brain networks for\nempathy and loving-kindness are different."},{"time":652335,"text":"Now, that's all well done,"},{"time":654416,"text":"so we got that from evolution,\nfrom maternal care, parental love,"},{"time":659790,"text":"but we need to extend that."},{"time":661625,"text":"It can be extended even to other species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664968,"text":"Now, if we want a more altruistic society,\nwe need two things:"},{"time":669375,"text":"individual change and societal change."},{"time":672592,"text":"So is individual change possible?"},{"time":675150,"text":"Two thousand years\nof contemplative study said yes, it is."},{"time":678349,"text":"Now, 15 years of collaboration\nwith neuroscience and epigenetics"},{"time":681951,"text":"said yes, our brains change\nwhen you train in altruism."},{"time":686435,"text":"So I spent 120 hours in an MRI machine."},{"time":690707,"text":"This is the first time I went\nafter two and a half hours."},{"time":693493,"text":"And then the result has been published\nin many scientific papers."},{"time":697167,"text":"It shows without ambiguity\nthat there is structural change"},{"time":700749,"text":"and functional change in the brain\nwhen you train the altruistic love."},{"time":704502,"text":"Just to give you an idea:"},{"time":706252,"text":"this is the meditator at rest on the left,"},{"time":709073,"text":"meditator in compassion meditation,\nyou see all the activity,"},{"time":712776,"text":"and then the control group at rest,\nnothing happened,"},{"time":715330,"text":"in meditation, nothing happened."},{"time":717272,"text":"They have not been trained."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719250,"text":"So do you need 50,000 hours \nof meditation? No, you don't."},{"time":723671,"text":"Four weeks, 20 minutes a day,\nof caring, mindfulness meditation"},{"time":727838,"text":"already brings a structural change\nin the brain compared to a control group."},{"time":734141,"text":"That's only 20 minutes a day\nfor four weeks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737879,"text":"Even with preschoolers --\nRichard Davidson did that in Madison."},{"time":741217,"text":"An eight-week program: gratitude, loving-\nkindness, cooperation, mindful breathing."},{"time":747627,"text":"You would say, \n\"Oh, they're just preschoolers.\""},{"time":749882,"text":"Look after eight weeks,"},{"time":751508,"text":"the pro-social behavior,\nthat's the blue line."},{"time":753958,"text":"And then comes the ultimate\nscientific test, the stickers test."},{"time":759402,"text":"Before, you determine for each child\nwho is their best friend in the class,"},{"time":763350,"text":"their least favorite child,\nan unknown child, and the sick child,"},{"time":767425,"text":"and they have to give stickers away."},{"time":770129,"text":"So before the intervention,\nthey give most of it to their best friend."},{"time":774181,"text":"Four, five years old, \n20 minutes three times a week."},{"time":777640,"text":"After the intervention,\nno more discrimination:"},{"time":781123,"text":"the same amount of stickers to their \nbest friend and the least favorite child."},{"time":785048,"text":"That's something we should do\nin all the schools in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":788436,"text":"Now where do we go from there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":790430,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":794678,"text":"When the Dalai Lama heard that,\nhe told Richard Davidson,"},{"time":797359,"text":"\"You go to 10 schools, 100 schools,\nthe U.N., the whole world.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":800815,"text":"So now where do we go from there?"},{"time":802499,"text":"Individual change is possible."},{"time":804762,"text":"Now do we have to wait for an altruistic \ngene to be in the human race?"},{"time":809378,"text":"That will take 50,000 years,\ntoo much for the environment."},{"time":813132,"text":"Fortunately, there is\nthe evolution of culture."},{"time":817567,"text":"Cultures, as specialists have shown,\nchange faster than genes."},{"time":823301,"text":"That's the good news."},{"time":824829,"text":"Look, attitude towards war\nhas dramatically changed over the years."},{"time":828189,"text":"So now individual change and cultural \nchange mutually fashion each other,"},{"time":833370,"text":"and yes, we can achieve\na more altruistic society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836146,"text":"So where do we go from there?"},{"time":837888,"text":"Myself, I will go back to the East."},{"time":840137,"text":"Now we treat 100,000 patients\na year in our projects."},{"time":843597,"text":"We have 25,000 kids in school,\nfour percent overhead."},{"time":847346,"text":"Some people say, \"Well,\nyour stuff works in practice,"},{"time":849921,"text":"but does it work in theory?\""},{"time":851945,"text":"There's always positive deviance."},{"time":855287,"text":"So I will also go back to my hermitage"},{"time":857706,"text":"to find the inner resources\nto better serve others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860995,"text":"But on the more global level,\nwhat can we do?"},{"time":864182,"text":"We need three things."},{"time":865973,"text":"Enhancing cooperation:"},{"time":868325,"text":"Cooperative learning in the school\ninstead of competitive learning,"},{"time":872041,"text":"Unconditional cooperation\nwithin corporations --"},{"time":875612,"text":"there can be some competition\nbetween corporations, but not within."},{"time":880019,"text":"We need sustainable harmony.\nI love this term."},{"time":883971,"text":"Not sustainable growth anymore."},{"time":885914,"text":"Sustainable harmony means now\nwe will reduce inequality."},{"time":889500,"text":"In the future, we do more with less,"},{"time":893826,"text":"and we continue to grow qualitatively,\nnot quantitatively."},{"time":898310,"text":"We need caring economics."},{"time":900615,"text":"The Homo economicus cannot deal\nwith poverty in the midst of plenty,"},{"time":906446,"text":"cannot deal with the problem\nof the common goods"},{"time":908798,"text":"of the atmosphere, of the oceans."},{"time":911096,"text":"We need a caring economics."},{"time":912679,"text":"If you say economics\nshould be compassionate,"},{"time":914788,"text":"they say, \"That's not our job.\""},{"time":916273,"text":"But if you say they don't care,\nthat looks bad."},{"time":919588,"text":"We need local commitment,\nglobal responsibility."},{"time":922967,"text":"We need to extend altruism\nto the other 1.6 million species."},{"time":928307,"text":"Sentient beings \nare co-citizens in this world."},{"time":931732,"text":"and we need to dare altruism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":934724,"text":"So, long live the altruistic revolution."},{"time":938605,"text":"Viva la revolución de altruismo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":943155,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":948515,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":950496,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}